result.name: Chao Chao Gyoza

reviews.text: Great hole in the wall with some great simple eats. Chao Chao gyozas and a beer make a great snack.

They have many different flavors of Japanese dumplings in their menu. We have ordered six different flavors. All of them are pretty good. The one I like most is the basic one (called Chao Chao in the menu) which is also said to be No. 1  in popularity. The shrimp dumplings are also nice.
Nice and quick place to get some good gyoza. Nothing too special, bit doors the job really well and the speed of the service is a godsend if you're stretched for time.
Great for quick bit of dumplings and beer
Delicious dumplings, can eat alot…

result.name: 餃餃餃子 (鰂魚涌分店)

reviews.text: 即棄筷子有陣漂白水臭味算唔算係大問題？咁如果碟餃子有條毛咁又。。。？ 雖然餃子同黃埔一樣都係咁好食，但呢啲細節都唔處理好就真係好嚇人。( 廁所打理得乾淨同好服務值樓上1粒星)
好好美味！餃子皮好薄又好多餡料選擇，我喜歡蒜香餃子、海老餃子，好香好好味！蝦好彈牙、好新鮮、好彈牙；蒜蓉好香、好美味喔
价錢還算适中 味道一般吧
餃子個餡好味夠脆
